portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">lookback option</a> is=C2=A0<em>=
incredibly incredibly valuable</em>.[1] Well. I mean, it is valuable in the=
ory. On certain assumptions. It is valuable=C2=A0if they pay you. The probl=
em is that if the fund goes to zero and you say =E2=80=9CI would like to ge=
t paid as though the fund was still worth $36 billion, like my contract say=
s,=E2=80=9D they will say =E2=80=9Csure buddy we=E2=80=99d all like that bu=
t where do you think the money will come from?=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">Here is a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/28276298.281582/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaX=
